This repository is a reference / teaching scaffold for a self-driving-car demo
on the AUTOSAR Adaptive Platform. It is not intended for deployment on a real
vehicle. The MIT license above covers only the original code authored in this
repository. The components below are the property of their respective authors
and remain governed by their own licenses.

1. Adaptive-AUTOSAR  (included as a git submodule)
   Source:   https://github.com/tatsuyai713/Adaptive-AUTOSAR
   Copyright (c) tatsuyai713 and contributors.
   License:  MIT License.
   Its code is not copied into this repository; the submodule references the
   upstream commit. See that repository's LICENSE file, which governs its use.

2. lwrcl - LightWeight Rclcpp Compatible Library  (included as a git submodule)
   Source:   https://github.com/tatsuyai713/lwrcl
   Copyright (c) tatsuyai713 and contributors.
   License:  Apache License, Version 2.0.
   Its code is not copied into this repository; the submodule references the
   upstream commit. See that repository's LICENSE and NOTICE files, which
   govern its use. Any modifications made under this project are noted at the
   point of change, as required by the Apache 2.0 license.

3. Udacity Self-Driving Car materials  (reference only)
   Source:   https://github.com/udacity
   Portions of the av_stack algorithm cores - perception, localization
   (EKF), planning, and control - were developed with reference to Udacity's
   open self-driving-car course repositories. Those original materials remain
   the property of Udacity and its contributors and are governed by their own
   respective licenses; consult each Udacity repository's LICENSE file. This
   project claims no ownership over Udacity's original works and reproduces no
   substantial portion of their code verbatim; they served as an educational
   reference for the algorithmic approaches re-implemented here.
